Centum Shareholders Approve Rwanda, Tanzania Cross-Listing

-- B y   J o h n s t o n e   O l e   T u r a n a
-- 
2011-09-23T12:19:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-23/centum-shareholders-approve-rwanda-tanzania-cross-listing.html
Centum Investment Co., a Kenya-
based  investment company , said shareholders approved plans to
begin trading its shares in neighboring Tanzania and Rwanda.  Shareholders also voted in favor of a bonus stock offer of
one new share for every 10 held, Chairman James Muguiyi said at
an annual general meeting today in Nairobi, the capital.  “These approvals allow us to finalize our plan for
geographical expansion by extending our ownership across the
region and also set up investment vehicles for investment
outside  Kenya ,” Muguiyi said.  Shareholders approved the formation of subsidiaries in
Uganda and Mauritius. The company aims to expand to Rwanda,
Uganda, Tanzania and Zimbabwe, Chief Executive Officer James Mworia said.  “We are looking at these markets for new opportunities
with the main focus on the consumer market where we have
considerable knowledge from current operations,” he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
